Class PThemeImageIcon

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.ImageIcon
      • com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.swing.PImageIconAsync
        • com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.swing.theme.PThemeImageIcon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Accessible, Icon

    @FullyTested
public class PThemeImageIcon
extends PImageIconAsync
    Extends PImageIconAsync for standard themes. This class is intended as an output from a theme icon loader, e.g., PThemeIconLoaderFixedDimensionFromPngFile.
    Author:
    Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
    See Also:
    PThemeIconLoaderAbstract, PThemeIconLoaderAbstractFixedDimension, PThemeIconLoaderFixedDimensionFromPngFile, Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • PThemeImageIcon

        public PThemeImageIcon(PImmutableDimension expectedDimension,
               PThemeIconName name,
               URL url)
        Create an icon from a standard theme. Normally, this constructor should be called indirectly by PThemeIconLoaderAbstract.tryGetIcon(PThemeIconName) or PThemeIconLoaderAbstract.getIcon(PThemeIconName).

        The icon description (ImageIcon.getDescription()) is generated from:

        • name.baseFileName - PThemeIconName.baseFileName
        • expectedDimension.getDescription() - PImmutableDimension.getDescription()

        Example description: "application-exit:22x22"

        Parameters:
        expectedDimension - see PImageIconAsync.getExpectedDimension(). Must not be null
        name - see getThemeIconName(). Must not be null
        url - see getUrl(). Must not be null
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if expectedDimension, name, or url is null
        See Also:
        PThemeIconLoaderAbstract, PImageIconAsync.updateImageLoadStatus(), PImageIconAsync.waitForLoad(long)
